+### 3.1 `src/utils/boundaryDetector.js` のインターフェース
+
+```js
+/**
+ * boundaryDetector.js
+ * 
+ * Pure utility for detecting semantic boundaries (chapter, section,
+ * paragraph) in Japanese novel text.
+ * 
+ * Used as a building block for future segmentation features.
+ * 
+ * This module has no side effects and no external dependencies.
+ */
+
+/**
+ * @typedef {Object} BoundaryCandidate
+ * @property {number} offset - Character offset (0-indexed) where the boundary
+ *   would be placed. The boundary sits between text[offset-1] and text[offset].
+ *   Zero is never returned (boundary at start of text is meaningless).
+ * @property {'chapter' | 'section' | 'paragraph' | 'sentence'} type
+ * @property {string} marker - The matched text (e.g. "■", "第1章", "# ")
+ * @property {number} confidence - 0.0 to 1.0, for ranking candidates
+ *   - 1.0: explicit chapter marker (■, 第N章, etc.)
+ *   - 0.8: section marker (triple blank lines, ［＃改ページ］)
+ *   - 0.5: paragraph boundary (single blank line)
+ *   - 0.3: sentence boundary (after 。)
+ * @property {{ before: string, after: string }} context
+ *   - before: up to 200 chars immediately preceding the boundary
